                        "content": "<p>The nurse overhears a neurologist saying that a client has an aneurysm located in the circle of Willis. The nurse understands that which blood vessels are part of the circle of Willis? Select all that apply.</p>",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "c2472dbaf30269ec1d4a4af474a31869",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Understanding 理解",
                        "textAnalysis": "<p>Rationale:</p><p>The circle of Willis is a ring of blood vessels located at the base of the brain. It is referred to as the anterior circulation to the brain and is composed of the anterior and middle cerebral arteries, posterior cerebral arteries, posterior communicating arteries, internal carotid arteries, and anterior communicating branches. The basilar artery and vertebral artery are not part of the circle of Willis. Rather, they are part of the vertebral-basilar system, which is known as the posterior circulation to the brain. Other parts of the posterior circulation are the posterior inferior cerebellar artery and the spinal arteries.</p>",
                        "id": "1a31766e43af48acbabfca72e7d02e1f",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "34d04ed0f5774ee1b1b79e3184ee6544",
                                "content": "Leave the lights on in the client's room at night."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "dcb05aac7b694adaa1d13970a76b6bc9",
                                "content": "Place a blood pressure cuff at the client's bedside."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "2d4e64ee38a0483893add9b9eaa213ab",
                                "content": "Close the shades in the client's room during the day."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "587741bccde645d186f29ff523ea09b4",
                                "content": "Allow the client to drink 1 cup of caffeinated coffee a day."
